### Number of Awards

One (1)

### Value

J$100,000 

### Maximum Tenure

One (1) year.

### Eligibilty

The award is available to Jamaican students who are:

  - Registered full-time in the Faculty of Science & Technology or Social Sciences;
  - Alumnus of Kingston College;
  - Between the ages of 20-25 years (at the time of application);
  - Entering the final year of their degree programme.
  
 
### Criteria

The award will be based on:

  - strong academic performnce ( at least a GPA of 3.0);
  - verifiable financial need;
  - demonstrable involvement in co-curricular/community involvement;
  - leadership qualities.

### Method of Selection

Shortlisted candidates will be interviewed by personnel from the UWI & the Donors.

### Number of Awards

One (1)

### Value


J$50,000

### Maximum Tenure

One (1) year.

### Eligibilty

The award is available to Jamaican nationals who are:
  
  - registered in an Undergraduate programme;
  - between the ages of 18 & 23 years at the time of application;
  - entering Levels One (1), Two (2) or Three (3) of their programme;
  - alumni of Glenmuir High School and/or resident of May Pen, Clarendon.

  
 
### Criteria

The award will be based on:

  - academic performance based on the previous academic years' UWI examinations for students in Year 2 or 3 (a GPA of at least 3.0);
  - CSEC/CAPE results for students in Yaer 1;
  - verifiable financial need;
  - demonstrable leadership qualities and committment to volunteerism.

### Method of Selection

Shortlisted candidates will be interviewed by a panel including:
  - Mrs. Sylvia Henry or any member of the Henry family;
  - UWIDEF and UWI representatives;
  - Any other designee(s) as required by the Henry family.

### Condition

The recipient will be required to maintain a record of behaviour acceptable to the UWI Mona.
